Write a C program that includes a function to determine if a given integer is a perfect square. The function should iterate only up to the square root of the number. The function signature is:
bool isPerfectSquare(int n);

Do not use any built-in functions that directly check for perfect squares or return the square root. Instead, implement your own logic that uses the <math.h> library for square root calculations.

#include <stdbool.h>
#include <math.h>

bool isPerfectSquare(int n) {
    if (n < 0) {
        return false;
    }
    int root = (int)sqrt(n);
    return root * root == n;
}

